<br>
Chuk, snippets from the same post addressed your inquiries.<br>
<br>
Question: I must be missing something here.<br>
You guys dont mind getting AA skills, you like PoP, but the idea of new levels would be too much?<br>
<br>
Answer: Post #9 &quot;In short- yes, it's too much to ask for me to level 5 more levels. People grow and what once appealed to them rarely holds the same appeal after this much time. &quot;<br>
<br>
Question: Why has raising the levels changed any of those things for you? <br>
<br>
Answer: Post #12 &quot;I'm not going to quit purely because of the levels issue, but because of the tedium and monotony... Already sick of the game but held out until more info about the upcoming expansion was released to see if it'd be worth my while to stay with it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Basically, this is why we're in R&amp;F right now-  <br>
<br>
1. People already unhappy with EQ and are already MIA from the game.<br>
2. People don't like what's coming with PoP.<br>
3. People have no reason to continue since PoP was the last incentive.<br>
4. People officially quit and cancel subscription.<br>
<br>
That is what's going on in my head, at least.  But, Razer got a little ahead of himself and saw it this way-<br>
<br>
1. People don't like PoP.<br>
2. People quit because of PoP.<br>
<br>
See how two major points are missing from the latter?  It's not an issue of being dissatisfied with PoP, it's an issue of general dissatisfaction with EQ, which is what I've been emphasizing all along.<br>
<br>
So, Razer hopped in and defended PoP and asserted we were quitting because of PoP, which would be a stupid thing to do <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> if</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> we were still happy playing EQ.  We're not stupid.  We know exactly what we're doing and have our own valid reasons for doing so, and didn't appreciate getting tied in with stupid motives.  And that's how the flames began. <p>- Aishen<br>
